<h2 id="bottom-line">The Bottom Line</h2>

<p>Ghana's real estate sector has real demand, improving cost dynamics, and a structural housing deficit that will persist for decades. The sector score of 7.2/10 is earned.</p>

<p>But real estate is the single most dangerous sector for diaspora investors operating remotely. The combination of land tenure fragility, construction supervision requirements, and the impossibility of remote quality control creates a risk profile that no amount of optimism can overcome.</p>

<p>If you are in the diaspora and considering Ghana real estate: visit first, verify everything twice, budget 150% of expectations, and do not confuse the housing deficit with a safe investment. The deficit is real. Your ability to profit from it, from thousands of miles away, is the question GhanaWorld cannot answer with a score above 5.0.</p>

